.XS
Building CASUP
.XE
.PP
To build CASUP do (adjust for your environment):
.DS L
.CW
mkdir \[Do]HOME/casup
mkdir \[Do]HOME/lib
.DE
.PP
On some platforms, e.g. when using the Intel Fortran
compiler, separate module files, extension
.CW .mod ,
will be created.
On such platforms add a directory to store the module files, e.g.:
.DS L
.CW
mkdir \[Do]HOME/mod
.DE
.PP
Then put the source code somewhere, e.g.:
.DS L
.CW
cd \[Do]HOME/casup
svn co https://svn.code.sf.net/p/cgpack/code/ .
.DE
.PP
And build using one of the provided
.CW Makefile s,
adjusting for your environment, e.g.:
.DS L
.CW 
cd head
make -f Makefile-mpiifort
make -f Makefile-mpiifort install
.DE
This will build the library under
.CW \[Do]HOME/casup
and install it under
.CW \[Do]HOME/lib/libcasup.a .
If separate module files were built too, these
will be installed under
.CW \[Do]HOME/mod .
